        "subject": "LU-6768 lvfs: unmap reallocated blocks",
        "message": "LU-6768 lvfs: unmap reallocated blocks\n\ncall ll_unmap_underlying_metadata() on every allocated\nblock. otherwise metadata blocks released in a previous\ntransaction can be written by the kernel corrupting\nuser's data. pblock != 0 should be a good sign of that.\n\nThis patch is back-ported from the following one:\nLustre-commit: bcef61a80ab4fa6cee847722184738ba4deeb971\nLustre-change: http://review.whamcloud.com/15593\n\nSigned-off-by: Alex Zhuravlev <alexey.zhuravlev@intel.com>\nChange-Id: I415bb568851d254473a49dfadca9cea69165e283"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/b2_5"
    }
